  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> and slice into rings, 1 per person, then dice the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> onion rings</strong> and<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>to a shallow bowl and set aside to pickle until serving – these are your <strong>quick-pickled onion rings</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1643618986513-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1643618986513-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1643618986513-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1643618986513-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1643618986513-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the softened onion and cook for 1 min further, then set aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643618981967-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643618981967-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643618981967-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643618981967-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1643618981967-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and separate the <strong>outer leaves</strong>, then finely shred the <strong>inner core[s]</strong></p><p>Drain and finely dice your <strong>pineapple</strong></p><p>Tip: Don’t chuck pineapple juice down the drain. Instead, add it to your smoothies, cakes or marinades!</p><p>Combine the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>,<strong> diced pineapple </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) in a bowl with plenty of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>pineapple salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1643618992126-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1643618992126-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1643618992126-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1643618992126-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1643618992126-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> as finely as you can, including the stalks</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>in a bowl – this is your <strong>herby mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1643618994821-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1643618994821-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1643618994821-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1643618994821-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1643618994821-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped basa </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix until the basa is evenly coated – this is your <strong>coated basa</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1643618998459-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1643618998459-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1643618998459-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1643618998459-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1643618998459-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until cooked through – this is your <strong>smoky basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1643619002346-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1643619002346-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1643619002346-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1643619002346-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1643619002346-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tortillas </strong>to a plate and pop them in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 20 secs on high or until warmed through</p><p>Drain the<strong> quick-pickled onion rings</strong> and discard the liquid</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-tortillas-on-a-plate-1663668182988-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-tortillas-on-a-plate-1663668182988-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-tortillas-on-a-plate-1663668182988-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-tortillas-on-a-plate-1663668182988-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-tortillas-on-a-plate-1663668182988-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top your <strong>warmed tortillas</strong> with a dollop of <strong>herby mayo </strong>and the<strong> lettuce leaves</strong></p><p>Fill the lettuce leaves with the <strong>softened onion</strong>, top with <strong>smoky basa</strong>, <strong>pineapple salsa</strong> and garnish with the <strong>quick-pickled onion rings</strong> – these are your<strong> smoky basa, pineapple & red onion tacos</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
